Yes, if your code is structured with modules and you want to import from outside the current crate, then you need to specify the correct path. Like this:
```rust
mod printable {
    pub trait Printable {
        fn print(&self);
    }
}
use crate::printable::Printable;
```
This way Rust knows exactly which `Printable` you're referring to.

